<br>
On the rapidly-developing beggar tangent/thread hijacking, and specifically to calare <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , here's a success story. (All quotes are paraphrased, but pretty close.)<br>
<br>
I received a tell from a newbie in Cabilis the other night, &quot;Hello brother Iksar&quot; or something similarly RPish, so I replied, and he said he was new and asked me if I had an item for him to get started.<br>
<br>
He was being polite and speaking reasonably RP-like in complete sentences, so I decided to be nice, and asked if his guildmaster hadn't given him a dagger or something to get started (I caught a glance of him as I was leaving the Warsliks gate and he was a necro).<br>
<br>
&quot;I only have the dagger I started with,&quot; says he.<br>
&quot;Well,&quot; says I, &quot;there you go. That should serve you well enough until you can earn a better weapon.&quot;<br>
<br>
Then he asks if I could help him find some good things to hunt. I ask him if his guildmaster gave him any particular tasks to fulfill. I said I wasn't familiar with the tasks generally given to young bonecasters but if he could tell me what he needed, I'd be happy to tell him where to find it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh yes, I need to get some Sarnak brains.&quot;<br>
&quot;Ah,&quot; I reply, &quot;well, I know where you can find all kinds of Sarnaks wandering around - they're just outside the gates of the Lake of Ill Omen - but I think they're a bit more than a match for you yet. You should probably hunt some smaller things for practice first.&quot;<br>
&quot;That's what I thought,&quot; he says. &quot;But I'm having a hard time finding anything. Do you have any bonechips I could borrow?&quot;<br>
<br>
Well, I didn't have any bonechips on me (and that's one thing I really don't mind handing out to young necros, as long as they ask nicely), but I told him he should try the Field of Bone for hunting experience, and a place to gather chips. He asked where that was, and I offered to show him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Thanks!&quot; says he, and so I meet him back at the gate, and lead him to East Cabilis, where we make a quick stop at the Haggle Baron, and I help him get through the text with Mugruk about the curscale skins quest. Once he had his curscale collection pack, I took him to the FOB gate and told him to just follow the road straight out and he'd find all kinds of wolf pups to kill. He thanked me profusely and ran off to hunt.<br>
<br>
So keep the faith, some of those beggars out there really just don't know any better. Or worse, they bought one of those &quot;guides&quot; that advises begging, bleh. Of course, I had an idea this guy just didn't know any better to start with, since he was at least trying to stay RPish from the beginning. I don't know if there's any cure for the real d00dz. :P<br>
<br>
